1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,260 --> 00:01:38,129
=Episode 5=

3
00:01:38,320 --> 00:01:39,439
I only want my granddaughter!

4
00:01:39,440 --> 00:01:41,279
I can raise her.

5
00:01:41,280 --> 00:01:42,669
Mom, why don't you want the money?

6
00:01:42,670 --> 00:01:44,949
She should be paying for it.
That's child support.

7
00:01:44,950 --> 00:01:46,760
Shut up.

8
00:01:47,110 --> 00:01:47,879
Alright.

9
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:49,589
The court has heard

10
00:01:49,590 --> 00:01:50,949
both parties' positions and claims.

11
00:01:50,950 --> 00:01:51,469
The court...

12
00:01:51,470 --> 00:01:52,589
Your Honor,

13
00:01:52,590 --> 00:01:54,070
I'd like to say something.

14
00:01:54,470 --> 00:01:55,630
Go ahead.

15
00:01:55,750 --> 00:01:57,559
After several hearings,

16
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:59,749
I believe it's clear to the court

17
00:01:59,750 --> 00:02:01,240
that Ms. Sun Lala

18
00:02:01,310 --> 00:02:03,189
is not a qualified mother.

19
00:02:03,190 --> 00:02:04,710
Who do you think you are?

20
00:02:04,880 --> 00:02:06,309
Are you the judge?

21
00:02:06,310 --> 00:02:07,680
(Panel Judge)
Defendant.

22
00:02:07,960 --> 00:02:09,200
Do not interrupt.

23
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:11,399
Of course,

24
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:13,239
my client, Mr. Liu Wenbo,

25
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:15,350
is not a qualified father either.

26
00:02:16,070 --> 00:02:17,589
Are you serious?

27
00:02:17,590 --> 00:02:18,839
You're my lawyer.

28
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:20,230
I paid you.

29
00:02:20,630 --> 00:02:21,839
Order, please.

30
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:23,630
This is not your turn to speak.

31
00:02:28,470 --> 00:02:29,559
I understand

32
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:30,719
that under the law,

33
00:02:30,720 --> 00:02:32,159
after a divorce,

34
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:34,349
as long as one parent is capable
of raising the child,

35
00:02:34,350 --> 00:02:35,749
generally,

36
00:02:35,750 --> 00:02:37,679
grandparents on either side

37
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:40,239
do not have

38
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,959
independent custody rights.

39
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:44,159
Of course not.

40
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:44,789
Also,

41
00:02:44,790 --> 00:02:46,349
at her age,

42
00:02:46,350 --> 00:02:47,589
with that little income,

43
00:02:47,590 --> 00:02:49,349
it's not even enough for her medication.

44
00:02:49,350 --> 00:02:51,719
What if she dies?

45
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:52,879
What happens to my daughter then?

46
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:55,200
A child's growth
is not just about money.

47
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:02,320
Your Honor, members of the panel,

48
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:04,159
I respectfully ask you

49
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:05,760
to consider the possibility

50
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:06,789
of allowing Liu Yitian

51
00:03:06,790 --> 00:03:09,070
to live with her grandmother.

52
00:03:20,750 --> 00:03:21,950
I apologize.

53
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:23,510
I was

54
00:03:23,630 --> 00:03:24,959
a little emotional just now.

55
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:26,189
That's because

56
00:03:26,190 --> 00:03:28,230
I was raised by my grandmother too.

57
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:29,349
My grandmother

58
00:03:29,350 --> 00:03:30,789
was in a similar situation to Mrs. Liu.

59
00:03:30,790 --> 00:03:32,839
She was sick and poor.

60
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:35,230
She supported my father

61
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:36,839
with her sewing.

62
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:38,439
But my father didn't turn out well.

63
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:39,839
He drifted through life

64
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:41,280
and died young.

65
00:03:42,070 --> 00:03:43,760
My mother left too.

66
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:46,480
So I grew up with my grandmother.

67
00:03:47,630 --> 00:03:49,350
Back then,

68
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:52,040
she used to do laundry for people.

69
00:03:52,070 --> 00:03:55,560
The employers would provide meals.
But one day, she somehow got hepatitis.

70
00:03:56,720 --> 00:03:58,480
After that, no one
would hire her anymore.

71
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:02,110
So she had to beg for food
from one household,

72
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:04,910
then another, just to raise me.

73
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:09,440
Later, she gave up looking for job.

74
00:04:09,790 --> 00:04:12,390
She started growing vegetables,
selling them, drying goods,

75
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:14,880
and even picking up scrap to sell.

76
00:04:16,830 --> 00:04:18,510
It wasn't until I grew a bit older

77
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:20,510
and could help her

78
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:22,510
that life slowly got better.

79
00:04:25,190 --> 00:04:26,389
I know,

80
00:04:26,390 --> 00:04:28,390
hearing this, you'd probably think

81
00:04:28,950 --> 00:04:30,920
I had a really hard childhood.

82
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:32,680
That I suffered a lot.

83
00:04:33,710 --> 00:04:35,680
But it wasn't like that.

84
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:39,000
Because ever since I can remember,
I've been with my grandmother.

85
00:04:39,270 --> 00:04:40,629
When I look back now,

86
00:04:40,630 --> 00:04:42,200
all I remember is happiness.

87
00:04:43,190 --> 00:04:45,830
Because my grandmother
never raised her voice at me.

88
00:04:46,270 --> 00:04:48,470
She never let anyone bully me.

89
00:04:49,150 --> 00:04:50,439
When I envied other kids

90
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:52,679
who had new clothes and pretty dresses,

91
00:04:52,680 --> 00:04:54,630
she would sew them for me

92
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:56,590
from leftover fabric.

93
00:04:57,390 --> 00:04:58,749
She'd even pick up dolls

94
00:04:58,750 --> 00:05:00,799
other kids threw away

95
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,150
and bring them home for me.

96
00:05:02,830 --> 00:05:07,510
I even had a brand-new,
authentic princess doll set.

97
00:05:08,070 --> 00:05:09,680
That was because

98
00:05:11,830 --> 00:05:13,800
she got hit by a luxury car.

99
00:05:15,190 --> 00:05:16,630
The hospital said

100
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:18,070
she needed tests.

101
00:05:18,630 --> 00:05:20,030
She refused.

102
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:22,440
She saw a brand-new doll set

103
00:05:22,510 --> 00:05:24,559
in the driver's car

104
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:27,829
and asked if she could have it.

105
00:05:27,830 --> 00:05:30,240
She said, "My granddaughter likes this."

106
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:36,200
That's my grandmother.

107
00:05:39,750 --> 00:05:41,630
I believe the girl's growth

108
00:05:41,950 --> 00:05:43,309
isn't just about money.

109
00:05:43,310 --> 00:05:44,960
What she really need
is someone who truly loves her,

110
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:46,069
stays by her side

111
00:05:46,070 --> 00:05:47,800
and lets her feel that love.

112
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:50,710
Only then will she learn
how to love others.

113
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:54,120
That will be a lifelong asset for her.

114
00:06:06,390 --> 00:06:08,200
That's all I have to say.

115
00:06:17,990 --> 00:06:19,309
The court is adjourned for deliberation.

116
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:22,400
(Hearing in progress)

117
00:06:24,270 --> 00:06:25,749
Looking at this family,

118
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:27,950
the grandmother is the only reasonable one.

119
00:06:28,310 --> 00:06:31,200
I agree with Ms. Qin.

120
00:06:31,250 --> 00:06:32,799
With the family's
current financial situation,

121
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:35,119
the child won't go hungry
no matter who she lives with.

122
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:36,749
But what matters most
in a child's growth

123
00:06:36,750 --> 00:06:39,269
is having someone by her side

124
00:06:39,270 --> 00:06:40,749
who truly cares for her,

125
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:42,709
loves her, and protects her.

126
00:06:42,710 --> 00:06:44,559
I support
awarding custody to the plaintiff.

127
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:45,709
If custody goes to the father,

128
00:06:45,710 --> 00:06:46,879
in reality, the child

129
00:06:46,880 --> 00:06:48,440
will be raised by the grandmother.

130
00:06:53,150 --> 00:06:55,510
The plaintiff's
closing argument was very moving.

131
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:56,479
And I do believe

132
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:57,509
Xiaolongbao's grandmother

133
00:06:57,510 --> 00:06:59,709
is the one who truly loves
the child the most.

134
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:02,359
However, there is one issue
we can't ignore.

135
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:05,269
Every elderly person's
health condition is different.

136
00:07:05,270 --> 00:07:06,389
Qin Rui's grandmother

137
00:07:06,390 --> 00:07:08,239
was able to raise her

138
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:09,879
despite being ill.

139
00:07:09,880 --> 00:07:11,320
But that's not something
you can count on.

140
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:12,479
Let's not even mention that

141
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,309
Xiaolongbao's grandmother
has heart problems.

142
00:07:14,310 --> 00:07:15,799
Even elderly people

143
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:17,709
who seem perfectly healthy,

144
00:07:17,710 --> 00:07:20,359
there's still a chance

145
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:22,149
they could pass away suddenly

146
00:07:22,150 --> 00:07:24,360
from a cold, a fall,

147
00:07:24,390 --> 00:07:26,710
or even just lying down for a nap.

148
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:28,389
Let's say,

149
00:07:28,390 --> 00:07:30,680
if Xiaolongbao's grandmother
were to pass away unexpectedly,

150
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:32,559
are we really going to put the child

151
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:34,830
through another custody battle?

152
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:39,189
The average life expectancy
for women in China is around eighty.

153
00:07:39,190 --> 00:07:42,950
Why assume she'd be the exception?

154
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:45,559
Just because you're afraid of losing
something, you give everything up?

155
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:47,779
Just because you're afraid of setbacks,
you stop chasing your dreams?

156
00:07:47,779 --> 00:07:49,920
Then what about you?
You're afraid something might go wrong,

157
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:51,270
so you keep putting off having a child.

158
00:07:51,390 --> 00:07:53,829
Is that the same?
I never said I don't want kids.

159
00:07:53,830 --> 00:07:55,779
I just want a good starting point

160
00:07:55,780 --> 00:07:57,560
to give my child
the best possible security.

161
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:02,200
Why are you making this personal?

162
00:08:03,070 --> 00:08:05,360
I'm just focusing on the issue.

163
00:08:05,390 --> 00:08:06,680
Apologize.

164
00:08:07,390 --> 00:08:08,920
I'm sorry, Le.

165
00:08:10,190 --> 00:08:11,630
You are forgiven.

166
00:08:11,880 --> 00:08:13,320
Back to the case.

167
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:15,390
If what you said is true,

168
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:17,629
if Xiaolongbao's grandmother,

169
00:08:17,630 --> 00:08:18,559
in the worst-case scenario,

170
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:20,149
suddenly passes away,

171
00:08:20,150 --> 00:08:23,389
and the father is unable or

172
00:08:23,390 --> 00:08:25,389
fails to provide proper care,

173
00:08:25,390 --> 00:08:26,999
then it's still possible for the court

174
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,510
to reconsider

175
00:08:28,630 --> 00:08:30,039
and award custody to the mother.

176
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:31,269
At least, we tried

177
00:08:31,270 --> 00:08:33,520
to get the best possible outcome, right?

178
00:08:33,550 --> 00:08:34,959
There's a saying...

179
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:36,400
How does it go?

180
00:08:36,630 --> 00:08:38,749
"Love doesn't wait. Money does.

181
00:08:38,750 --> 00:08:40,149
Love is rare.

182
00:08:40,150 --> 00:08:41,669
Money isn't."

183
00:08:41,670 --> 00:08:42,389
Right.

184
00:08:42,390 --> 00:08:44,669
But everything you said has a premise.

185
00:08:44,670 --> 00:08:45,669
"Love is enough".

186
00:08:45,670 --> 00:08:48,029
It only works when basic needs are met.

187
00:08:48,030 --> 00:08:50,149
Exactly. You're right.

188
00:08:50,150 --> 00:08:51,909
And also surrounded
by more than enough love.

189
00:08:51,910 --> 00:08:54,800
That's when they can grow up healthy,
whole, and without lasting scars.

190
00:08:55,750 --> 00:08:58,280
Ms. Qin is a good example.

191
00:08:58,720 --> 00:09:00,749
Her closing statement
was indeed very compelling.

192
00:09:00,750 --> 00:09:01,749
I will give her that.

193
00:09:01,750 --> 00:09:02,870
However,

194
00:09:03,430 --> 00:09:09,319
compressing nearly twenty years of her life
into two minutes,

195
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:12,029
the emotional impact depends entirely

196
00:09:12,030 --> 00:09:15,750
on the angle she chooses
to tell that story.

197
00:09:15,790 --> 00:09:17,079
Are you saying

198
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:19,280
Ms. Qin was emotionally manipulating us?

199
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:21,359
Not necessarily.

200
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:22,920
I'm just saying

201
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:25,110
that might not be the full picture.

202
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,470
What are you trying to say?

203
00:09:28,150 --> 00:09:32,040
She has some hidden, dark side?

204
00:09:32,430 --> 00:09:33,800
I didn't say that.

205
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:40,199
Look at me.

206
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:42,629
I look too pretty. I'm radiating.

207
00:09:42,630 --> 00:09:44,350
You look too good.

208
00:09:45,270 --> 00:09:46,160
Well...

209
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:47,559
You should make yourself
look more worn out.

210
00:09:47,559 --> 00:09:49,119
At least, your followers
will sympathize more.

211
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:49,999
Yeah.

212
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:52,990
If I look worse, maybe the judge
will sympathize too.

213
00:09:53,390 --> 00:09:54,549
Alright. That's enough makeup.

214
00:09:54,550 --> 00:09:56,830
Get me a cotton pad.

215
00:09:57,630 --> 00:10:00,640
Wipe some of this off.
Tone it down a bit.

216
00:10:02,030 --> 00:10:03,640
Can't look too polished.

217
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,200
Not too pretty.

218
00:10:06,670 --> 00:10:08,230
Look, if the lips are paler...

219
00:10:10,880 --> 00:10:12,440
What's wrong, Jing?

220
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:13,629
No, this won't do.

221
00:10:13,630 --> 00:10:15,040
We need to re-deliberate the case.

222
00:10:16,910 --> 00:10:18,959
Wipe off the blush.

223
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:20,770
The blush.

224
00:10:22,510 --> 00:10:24,959
After deliberation by the panel,

225
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:26,429
the court hereby rules as follows.

226
00:10:26,430 --> 00:10:26,999
First,

227
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,319
custody of the minor, Liu Yitian, shall,

228
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:30,350
from the effective date
of this judgment,

229
00:10:30,390 --> 00:10:32,470
be granted to the father,

230
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:35,140
Liu Wenbo,
with whom the child shall reside.

231
00:10:35,150 --> 00:10:36,029
Second,

232
00:10:36,030 --> 00:10:38,870
child support and custody arrangements.

233
00:10:39,150 --> 00:10:41,319
From the effective date
of this judgment,

234
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:42,789
the defendant, Sun Lala,

235
00:10:42,790 --> 00:10:45,509
shall pay the plaintiff, Liu Wenbo,
a monthly sum of 3,000 yuan

236
00:10:45,510 --> 00:10:47,319
as living expenses for the child

237
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:50,160
until the child reaches
the age of eighteen.

238
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:52,029
I object!

239
00:10:52,030 --> 00:10:53,669
I carried this child for ten months.

240
00:10:53,670 --> 00:10:55,280
On what grounds is custody given to him?

241
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:58,160
(Presiding Judge)
Defendant, don't disrupt the court order.

242
00:10:58,390 --> 00:10:59,879
Lala!

243
00:10:59,880 --> 00:11:01,750
Defendant, please remain silent.

244
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:03,879
I... I don't accept this ruling!

245
00:11:03,880 --> 00:11:04,789
If you disagree,

246
00:11:04,790 --> 00:11:06,909
you may file an appeal
with the Intermediate People's Court.

247
00:11:06,910 --> 00:11:08,509
However, if you continue
to disrupt proceedings,

248
00:11:08,510 --> 00:11:10,400
the court will order bailiffs
to remove you immediately.

249
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:11,599
Then I'll appeal!

250
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:13,350
I'll sue him!

251
00:11:13,380 --> 00:11:14,529
Lala, stop embarrassing yourself.

252
00:11:14,529 --> 00:11:15,669
Did you take his money?

253
00:11:15,670 --> 00:11:17,149
Lala, stop it!

254
00:11:17,150 --> 00:11:18,629
I'll sue you too!

255
00:11:18,630 --> 00:11:20,669
I'll sue every single one of you!

256
00:11:20,670 --> 00:11:22,599
None of you is getting away with this!

257
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:24,199
Just you wait!

258
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:24,879
Silence!

259
00:11:24,880 --> 00:11:26,110
(First Courtroom, Camera Four)
Shut up!

260
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:30,549
Come on. Get in the car.

261
00:11:30,550 --> 00:11:32,040
Follow me.

262
00:11:32,670 --> 00:11:34,040
There we go.

263
00:11:34,270 --> 00:11:36,400
My sweetheart.

264
00:11:41,390 --> 00:11:43,200
Mr. Liu!

265
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:45,239
Look,

266
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:46,669
we won the case for you.

267
00:11:46,670 --> 00:11:48,440
You've got custody of your child.

268
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:49,950
About the legal fees...

269
00:11:50,390 --> 00:11:52,479
Ms. Qin, you're really something.

270
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:54,710
I'm very satisfied

271
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:55,909
with the outcome.

272
00:11:55,910 --> 00:11:57,479
I won't dodge the payment.

273
00:11:57,480 --> 00:11:59,990
But the amount we agreed on
in the contract,

274
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:01,839
I'm afraid I can't afford it now.

275
00:12:01,840 --> 00:12:03,319
What do you mean?

276
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:05,230
You've seen my situation.

277
00:12:05,270 --> 00:12:06,879
I used to make good money,

278
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:09,230
mostly from live stream donations
with my daughter.

279
00:12:09,390 --> 00:12:11,160
But now the account's been banned.

280
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:13,119
I can't access the money inside.

281
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:14,669
And there's no way

282
00:12:14,670 --> 00:12:16,230
I can earn like that again.

283
00:12:17,390 --> 00:12:19,110
To put it simply,

284
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:20,549
I've got nothing left.

285
00:12:20,550 --> 00:12:22,710
I have no money. Just my life.
Do you want that?

286
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:25,470
The contract is in black and white.

287
00:12:25,510 --> 00:12:26,319
Then go ahead and sue me.

288
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:27,909
We're at the court, anyway.

289
00:12:27,910 --> 00:12:28,789
Mr. Liu,

290
00:12:28,790 --> 00:12:30,669
I've spent so much time and effort
on your case.

291
00:12:30,670 --> 00:12:32,079
You can't just walk away like this.

292
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:34,920
How about installments? What do you think?

293
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:36,470
Installments?

294
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:38,909
How many?

295
00:12:38,910 --> 00:12:41,350
Didn't the court order her
to pay me 3,000 a month?

296
00:12:41,550 --> 00:12:42,789
I'll give you 300 this month,

297
00:12:42,790 --> 00:12:44,029
and 300 every month after that.

298
00:12:44,030 --> 00:12:45,269
You can come collect it each time

299
00:12:45,270 --> 00:12:46,479
until it's fully paid.

300
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:47,710
Three hundred?

301
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:49,319
You're being unreasonable.

302
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:50,830
Move side. I need to drive.

303
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:52,870
Mr. Liu!

304
00:12:53,150 --> 00:12:55,029
Fine. You want installments, right?

305
00:12:55,030 --> 00:12:57,079
Miss a payment, and I will sue you.

306
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:58,879
I live right across the street.

307
00:12:58,880 --> 00:13:00,669
You are unbelievable.

308
00:13:00,670 --> 00:13:02,319
(Children's innocent smiles)

309
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:05,040
(can wash away the exhaustion
of the adult world.)

310
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:07,269
(The unconditional trust in their eyes)

311
00:13:07,270 --> 00:13:10,200
(is one of the life's warmest comforts.)

312
00:13:10,550 --> 00:13:11,440
(However,)

313
00:13:11,630 --> 00:13:14,199
(when this pure sincerity,
born of life itself)

314
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:17,070
(is turned into traffic and profit,)

315
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:18,549
(children are reduced)

316
00:13:18,550 --> 00:13:21,160
(to commodities to be priced and sold.)

317
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,749
(Their laughter and anger)

318
00:13:23,750 --> 00:13:26,070
(are carefully scripted.)

319
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:33,149
(Their physical and emotional well-being,
and their natural growth,)

320
00:13:33,150 --> 00:13:35,389
(are quietly sacrificed)

321
00:13:35,390 --> 00:13:36,950
(in their parents' pursuit
of fame and gain.)

322
00:13:38,430 --> 00:13:39,999
(Xiaolongbao's grandmother)

323
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:43,350
(can protect her for now.)

324
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:46,830
(But how long can that last?)

325
00:13:46,910 --> 00:13:48,749
(Beyond the courtroom,)

326
00:13:48,750 --> 00:13:50,669
(how many child influencers)

327
00:13:50,670 --> 00:13:52,429
(are controlled by scripts)

328
00:13:52,430 --> 00:13:54,599
(and losing the joy
of growing up naturally?)

329
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:56,669
(How many young shoulders)

330
00:13:56,670 --> 00:14:00,110
(are forced too early to carry
their parents' ambitions and greed?)

331
00:14:00,270 --> 00:14:03,950
(Their rights must be protected
by every one of us.)

332
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:12,830
You're back.

333
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:14,160
Almost ready.

334
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:28,750
Did Liu Wenbo stiff you again?

335
00:14:28,840 --> 00:14:30,440
That cheapskate

336
00:14:30,910 --> 00:14:32,320
refuses to pay.

337
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,119
Only gave me a 300 deposit.

338
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:35,870
Might as well have given nothing.

339
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:36,599
Lian,

340
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:38,549
if I ever take jobs
from people like that again,

341
00:14:38,550 --> 00:14:39,719
hang me up

342
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:40,749
and break my legs.

343
00:14:40,750 --> 00:14:43,749
Break your legs?
Then I'd have to take care of you.

344
00:14:43,750 --> 00:14:45,110
I'm not that dumb.

345
00:14:45,390 --> 00:14:47,950
Then just slap me hard.

346
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:50,239
Don't beat yourself up.

347
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:52,199
At least it wasn't a total waste.

348
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:54,239
You're still new,

349
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:55,950
and don't get to pick your jobs.

350
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:58,350
Food's here.

351
00:14:58,720 --> 00:15:00,200
Careful, it's hot.

352
00:15:04,080 --> 00:15:05,640
This smells amazing.

353
00:15:09,320 --> 00:15:10,830
Dig in.

354
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:13,200
Here you go.

355
00:15:13,750 --> 00:15:16,909
- Here you go. Eat more.
- I want some.

356
00:15:16,910 --> 00:15:19,350
Eat well to have the energy to work.

357
00:15:19,430 --> 00:15:20,560
Try it.

358
00:15:25,670 --> 00:15:26,800
So good.

359
00:15:31,670 --> 00:15:34,669
Finally get to eat mutton from Lian.

360
00:15:34,670 --> 00:15:36,789
You've been craving
for this every day at home.

361
00:15:36,790 --> 00:15:37,879
What's wrong with that?

362
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:39,959
Jing, look at her.
She's thinking about food all day.

363
00:15:39,960 --> 00:15:41,509
Eat as much as you want today.

364
00:15:41,510 --> 00:15:43,239
Welcome. Please come in.

365
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:45,440
(Lian Mutton Soup)

366
00:15:58,550 --> 00:15:59,640
Yongjiu.

367
00:16:00,080 --> 00:16:01,230
Yongjiu.

368
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:02,920
Long time no see.

369
00:16:03,790 --> 00:16:05,429
Perfect timing. The hotpot's ready.

370
00:16:05,430 --> 00:16:06,959
I have fresh chili oil today.

371
00:16:06,960 --> 00:16:08,079
Help yourselves with the sauce.

372
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:09,509
No one is leaving

373
00:16:09,510 --> 00:16:11,359
until you have eaten your fill.

374
00:16:11,360 --> 00:16:12,629
Yongjiu, when have I

375
00:16:12,630 --> 00:16:14,710
ever held back here?

376
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:15,999
Come on in.

377
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,280
Where's Fei?

378
00:16:18,910 --> 00:16:20,160
At the counter.

379
00:16:20,790 --> 00:16:22,040
Inside.

380
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:27,440
Fei, look what's here.

381
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:29,400
Fei.

382
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:36,160
What are you drawing?

383
00:16:40,550 --> 00:16:41,990
Fei.

384
00:16:49,790 --> 00:16:50,999
Let's go upstairs.

385
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:52,200
Alright.

386
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:53,640
We're going upstairs.

387
00:16:57,360 --> 00:16:58,230
Come on.

388
00:16:59,030 --> 00:17:00,830
Eat to your heart's content.

389
00:17:01,630 --> 00:17:03,160
I'm starving.

390
00:17:03,950 --> 00:17:05,519
Come on. Let me try.

391
00:17:05,520 --> 00:17:06,680
Here.

392
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:08,119
I'll do it.

393
00:17:08,120 --> 00:17:09,680
Nice.

394
00:17:13,430 --> 00:17:15,200
Lian is the best.

395
00:17:19,040 --> 00:17:20,270
Uh.

396
00:17:20,760 --> 00:17:22,680
I'll go grab some drinks downstairs.

397
00:17:27,470 --> 00:17:29,709
You two are really in syn now.

398
00:17:29,710 --> 00:17:31,600
Xiao Bing is a nice guy.

399
00:17:31,630 --> 00:17:33,039
He carries your purse.

400
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:35,189
My husband never does that.

401
00:17:35,190 --> 00:17:36,879
We've got some chemistry,

402
00:17:36,880 --> 00:17:38,759
but he's not as good as Yongjiu.

403
00:17:38,760 --> 00:17:40,230
What a decent spread

404
00:17:40,430 --> 00:17:41,640
Yongjiu prepared.

405
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:44,039
There's no big deal about this.

406
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:46,230
You don't marry a guy for his cooking.

407
00:17:46,990 --> 00:17:49,120
Jing, I wanted to ask.

408
00:17:49,150 --> 00:17:50,949
Why did you suddenly
change your mind earlier today?

409
00:17:50,950 --> 00:17:52,189
Did you see

410
00:17:52,190 --> 00:17:54,840
the iPad wallpaper of that guy

411
00:17:54,950 --> 00:17:57,310
who's always with Sun Lala?

412
00:17:59,800 --> 00:18:01,200
I didn't pay attention to that.

413
00:18:05,900 --> 00:18:06,790
Look.

414
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:08,990
This is the movie poster.

415
00:18:09,950 --> 00:18:11,279
It's about

416
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:15,240
a minor being abused

417
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:17,440
by her guardian.

418
00:18:19,710 --> 00:18:22,550
You mean that kind of abuse?

419
00:18:26,320 --> 00:18:27,429
So

420
00:18:27,430 --> 00:18:29,030
I'm worried that guy

421
00:18:29,060 --> 00:18:31,519
might have bad intentions
towards Xiaolongbao.

422
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:33,519
That could ruin her life.

423
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:34,989
Yeah. You did the right thing.

424
00:18:34,990 --> 00:18:37,680
Better safe than sorry.

425
00:18:38,230 --> 00:18:40,360
Right now, I'm just worried
about Granny's medical bills.

426
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:42,839
Last time she stopped treatment
for two months,

427
00:18:42,840 --> 00:18:44,840
there were already signs of fibrosis.

428
00:18:44,990 --> 00:18:46,759
If I don't send money again,

429
00:18:46,760 --> 00:18:48,429
who knows what will happen.

430
00:18:48,430 --> 00:18:51,229
I feel bad for Granny.

431
00:18:51,230 --> 00:18:53,920
She stuck with a useless granddaughter.

432
00:18:54,150 --> 00:18:56,400
If it comes to it, I'll ask my mom.

433
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:57,909
It's okay.

434
00:18:57,910 --> 00:19:00,359
Let's wait till the end of the month.
Maybe things will turn around.

435
00:19:00,360 --> 00:19:01,629
Why the end of the month?

436
00:19:01,630 --> 00:19:03,120
You think you'll get money by then?

437
00:19:03,430 --> 00:19:05,039
Weren't you counting on the legal fees

438
00:19:05,040 --> 00:19:07,440
from Liu Wenbo and Ms. Liu before?

439
00:19:11,640 --> 00:19:13,669
(Transfer received: 15,000 yuan)

440
00:19:13,670 --> 00:19:15,030
My goodness!

441
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:16,600
I have money!

442
00:19:18,910 --> 00:19:20,389
I have money!

443
00:19:20,390 --> 00:19:21,669
Lian, I really have money!

444
00:19:21,670 --> 00:19:23,230
Are you serious?

445
00:19:24,190 --> 00:19:25,319
Fifteen thousand.

446
00:19:25,320 --> 00:19:26,470
Look.

447
00:19:27,710 --> 00:19:29,389
Fifteen thousand.

448
00:19:29,390 --> 00:19:30,519
Where did it come from?

449
00:19:30,520 --> 00:19:31,920
No idea.

450
00:19:32,150 --> 00:19:34,759
Could Liu Wenbo have
suddenly grown a conscience?

451
00:19:34,760 --> 00:19:35,949
Unlikely.

452
00:19:35,950 --> 00:19:38,680
I worked with him for so long.
I never saw any sign of that.

453
00:19:39,280 --> 00:19:41,799
It's probably Ms. Liu Lihua.

454
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:44,270
Look, she originally should
pay me sixty thousand.

455
00:19:44,280 --> 00:19:46,519
Now there's fifty per cent left,

456
00:19:46,520 --> 00:19:47,949
that's thirty thousand.

457
00:19:47,950 --> 00:19:49,429
Lin and I split it evenly,

458
00:19:49,430 --> 00:19:50,790
so that's 15,000 each.

459
00:19:51,080 --> 00:19:52,600
Are you sure?

460
00:19:52,950 --> 00:19:53,709
Ask them.

461
00:19:53,710 --> 00:19:54,880
Ask them?

462
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:57,030
Fine, I'll ask.
What's there to be scared of?

463
00:19:58,990 --> 00:20:00,839
You shouldn't be drinking green tea now.

464
00:20:00,840 --> 00:20:01,469
Right.

465
00:20:01,470 --> 00:20:02,709
It's too cooling.

466
00:20:02,710 --> 00:20:05,239
It's better to drink black tea.

467
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:07,880
(My Retirement Plan)

468
00:20:11,360 --> 00:20:13,270
My pension is calling me.

469
00:20:16,390 --> 00:20:17,550
Lin,

470
00:20:18,630 --> 00:20:20,149
was that you who sent the money?

471
00:20:20,150 --> 00:20:21,599
My wife sent it.

472
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:22,990
Keep it up.

473
00:20:23,390 --> 00:20:24,319
So what money is this?

474
00:20:24,320 --> 00:20:27,149
Is it from Ms. Liu Lihua?

475
00:20:27,150 --> 00:20:28,360
Yeah.

476
00:20:28,430 --> 00:20:29,840
The divorce request

477
00:20:30,320 --> 00:20:31,319
got rejected.

478
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:32,600
That's great!

479
00:20:32,630 --> 00:20:33,119
Alright.

480
00:20:33,120 --> 00:20:35,120
That's all I wanted to ask.
I'll hang up then.

481
00:20:38,390 --> 00:20:39,189
So?

482
00:20:39,190 --> 00:20:41,230
It really was Ms. Liu Lihua.

483
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:43,400
That's wild.

484
00:20:43,760 --> 00:20:45,920
Before this, I told her

485
00:20:45,990 --> 00:20:48,389
she had to call Judge Shen herself,

486
00:20:48,390 --> 00:20:49,559
but she didn't want to.

487
00:20:49,560 --> 00:20:52,119
She said it would be embarrassing
in front of her husband.

488
00:20:52,120 --> 00:20:53,629
And Judge Shen said

489
00:20:53,630 --> 00:20:55,599
if she didn't withdraw
the case themselves,

490
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:57,550
he'd stick to the rules.

491
00:20:58,080 --> 00:21:00,750
So how did it suddenly get rejected?

492
00:21:02,520 --> 00:21:04,230
Did Machine Shen glitch?

493
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:07,440
Or did Ms. Liu suddenly change her mind?

494
00:21:08,230 --> 00:21:09,600
Doesn't seem likely.

495
00:21:11,430 --> 00:21:12,039
Yongjiu,

496
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:13,600
grab me a bottle of water.

497
00:21:13,630 --> 00:21:16,279
Why did you come down?
They're talking about a case?

498
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:17,600
Exactly.

499
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:19,389
Le's been holding it in
the whole ride.

500
00:21:19,390 --> 00:21:20,359
I have a feeling

501
00:21:20,360 --> 00:21:21,839
that if it weren't for the mutton soup,

502
00:21:21,840 --> 00:21:23,279
she'd have made me
get out of the car first

503
00:21:23,280 --> 00:21:25,640
and finish talking
before letting me back in.

504
00:21:26,120 --> 00:21:26,989
There's a table here.

505
00:21:26,990 --> 00:21:28,640
Let's sit. Come on.

506
00:21:34,360 --> 00:21:35,990
Good thing we're at your place.

507
00:21:36,040 --> 00:21:37,600
If this were at home,

508
00:21:38,040 --> 00:21:40,950
I'd have to go downstairs for a walk
while she talks cases.

509
00:21:41,910 --> 00:21:43,149
Family members of judges

510
00:21:43,150 --> 00:21:45,840
have to cooperate with the rules.

511
00:21:47,230 --> 00:21:49,790
It's fair here.

512
00:21:50,040 --> 00:21:51,840
When you were a judge,

513
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:53,319
you'd step out when talking cases,

514
00:21:53,320 --> 00:21:54,949
and she'd do the same for you.

515
00:21:54,950 --> 00:21:56,669
It's a different case for us.

516
00:21:56,670 --> 00:21:57,949
Back then, I handled

517
00:21:57,950 --> 00:21:59,629
criminal cases like murders and arson.

518
00:21:59,630 --> 00:22:01,600
They couldn't be talked about at home.

519
00:22:03,080 --> 00:22:04,360
Such a shame.

520
00:22:04,910 --> 00:22:07,119
If it weren't for what happened to Tong,

521
00:22:07,120 --> 00:22:08,879
Shu Jing and you would still be judges.

522
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:09,950
It was nice.

523
00:22:11,190 --> 00:22:13,510
Then you wouldn't have a place

524
00:22:13,560 --> 00:22:14,990
to get mutton soup.

525
00:22:19,670 --> 00:22:20,920
I heard

526
00:22:21,190 --> 00:22:22,710
Tong's about to be discharged.

527
00:22:24,560 --> 00:22:25,680
I heard about that.

528
00:22:27,600 --> 00:22:28,839
Being a judge,

529
00:22:28,840 --> 00:22:30,510
you're bound to offend people.

530
00:22:30,950 --> 00:22:31,909
Back then,

531
00:22:31,910 --> 00:22:33,039
Shu Jing and I

532
00:22:33,040 --> 00:22:34,319
were always so careful.

533
00:22:34,320 --> 00:22:35,990
We're afraid of
dragging our family into trouble.

534
00:22:36,390 --> 00:22:37,759
But still,

535
00:22:37,760 --> 00:22:39,389
because of Tong,

536
00:22:39,390 --> 00:22:40,880
things went wrong.

537
00:22:45,910 --> 00:22:47,790
She doesn't dare to talk now.

538
00:22:47,950 --> 00:22:49,709
Welcome. This way, please.

539
00:22:49,710 --> 00:22:50,949
Welcome. This way, please.

540
00:22:50,950 --> 00:22:51,359
Yongjiu.

541
00:22:51,360 --> 00:22:51,799
Coming.

542
00:22:51,800 --> 00:22:53,160
Business is booming.

543
00:22:54,670 --> 00:22:55,949
Xiao Bing, you're here too.

544
00:22:55,950 --> 00:22:56,440
Yeah.

545
00:22:56,670 --> 00:22:59,039
- Everything's set upstairs. Go on.
- Alright. We'll head up.

546
00:22:59,040 --> 00:22:59,989
Go on.

547
00:22:59,990 --> 00:23:02,360
Go upstairs. Everyone's here.
The ladies will stop discussing the case.

548
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:03,710
I'll go up first.

549
00:23:10,600 --> 00:23:13,200
Why not just call and ask?

550
00:23:14,190 --> 00:23:15,710
I don't dare.

551
00:23:15,880 --> 00:23:17,079
Why?

552
00:23:17,080 --> 00:23:18,429
If I call,

553
00:23:18,430 --> 00:23:19,839
Ms. Liu will realize

554
00:23:19,840 --> 00:23:20,629
I don't even know

555
00:23:20,630 --> 00:23:21,839
how the case was settled.

556
00:23:21,840 --> 00:23:23,669
What if she asks for the money back?

557
00:23:23,670 --> 00:23:24,759
What do I do then?

558
00:23:24,760 --> 00:23:28,080
Feel it out, obviously.

559
00:23:28,710 --> 00:23:30,880
You make a living talking.
Don't tell me I have to teach you that.

560
00:23:34,360 --> 00:23:35,440
(Liu Lihua)

561
00:23:42,180 --> 00:23:43,220
Hello?

562
00:23:43,360 --> 00:23:44,709
Ms. Liu.

563
00:23:44,710 --> 00:23:45,559
Ms. Qin,

564
00:23:45,560 --> 00:23:47,149
I didn't get the chance

565
00:23:47,150 --> 00:23:48,709
to thank you earlier.

566
00:23:48,710 --> 00:23:49,949
I've sent the money.

567
00:23:49,950 --> 00:23:51,200
Did you get it?

568
00:23:51,910 --> 00:23:53,709
Yes, I got it.

569
00:23:53,710 --> 00:23:54,909
So it really was you?

570
00:23:54,910 --> 00:23:56,229
Great! Thank you so much.

571
00:23:56,230 --> 00:23:57,880
Don't mention it.

572
00:23:58,360 --> 00:24:00,039
Promise you won't laugh.

573
00:24:00,040 --> 00:24:01,429
I need to tell you something.

574
00:24:01,430 --> 00:24:04,149
When Judge Shen called me today,

575
00:24:04,150 --> 00:24:06,189
I almost cried.

576
00:24:06,190 --> 00:24:08,669
You know, he usually

577
00:24:08,670 --> 00:24:10,230
looks so cold,

578
00:24:10,430 --> 00:24:13,120
but I didn't expect him
to be so understanding.

579
00:24:13,150 --> 00:24:14,640
Judge Shen

580
00:24:14,950 --> 00:24:18,200
called you himself?

581
00:24:18,390 --> 00:24:19,470
Yes.

582
00:24:19,630 --> 00:24:21,389
What did he say?

583
00:24:21,390 --> 00:24:23,599
He wanted to check with me

584
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:24,989
whether not getting a divorce

585
00:24:24,990 --> 00:24:27,039
was my own decision.

586
00:24:27,040 --> 00:24:28,559
Honestly, I was torn at the time.

587
00:24:28,560 --> 00:24:30,279
I didn't know if I should say it or not.

588
00:24:30,280 --> 00:24:31,990
I was scared

589
00:24:32,080 --> 00:24:34,559
he might let it slip later,

590
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:36,750
or include it in the judgment.

591
00:24:36,990 --> 00:24:38,709
If my husband found out,

592
00:24:38,710 --> 00:24:42,270
how could I face him again?

593
00:24:42,360 --> 00:24:44,079
But you know what he said?

594
00:24:44,080 --> 00:24:45,790
He told me not to worry.

595
00:24:45,910 --> 00:24:47,189
As long as he knew

596
00:24:47,190 --> 00:24:49,909
I chose to stay in the marriage

597
00:24:49,910 --> 00:24:51,879
after careful consideration,

598
00:24:51,880 --> 00:24:54,389
he wouldn't include it in the judgment

599
00:24:54,390 --> 00:24:56,189
or let my husband find out.

600
00:24:56,190 --> 00:24:58,669
How can someone be that understanding?

601
00:24:58,670 --> 00:25:00,759
And he's so young too.

602
00:25:00,760 --> 00:25:02,440
Understanding?

603
00:25:02,670 --> 00:25:03,790
Oh, absolutely.

604
00:25:04,150 --> 00:25:05,669
Judge Shen

605
00:25:05,670 --> 00:25:07,759
is very understanding.

606
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:11,949
He's known for that around Qingcheng.
Cold on the outside, warm on the inside.

607
00:25:11,950 --> 00:25:13,629
He may look distant,

608
00:25:13,630 --> 00:25:14,599
hard to approach,

609
00:25:14,600 --> 00:25:16,279
but deep down,

610
00:25:16,280 --> 00:25:18,080
he's really kind.

611
00:25:18,630 --> 00:25:21,750
As I said, there's no way
the court is going to grant a divorce.

612
00:25:23,120 --> 00:25:23,949
Alright then.

613
00:25:23,950 --> 00:25:25,920
I won't keep you.

614
00:25:26,560 --> 00:25:27,990
Thank you so much, really.

615
00:25:30,950 --> 00:25:33,230
It was Ms. Liu Lihua
who transferred the money.

616
00:25:34,390 --> 00:25:37,400
Shen Xiezhi called her.

617
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:40,550
Looks like the machine guy's glitched.

618
00:25:41,880 --> 00:25:44,469
(Maybe empathy can guide us)

619
00:25:44,470 --> 00:25:46,519
(to answer that balance
emotion, reason, and the law.)

620
00:25:46,520 --> 00:25:48,840
(It can also save families.)

621
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:50,689
(But that same empathy)

622
00:25:50,690 --> 00:25:51,469
Bill, please.

623
00:25:51,470 --> 00:25:54,079
(can also bring nightmares)

624
00:25:54,080 --> 00:25:57,270
(misunderstanding, retaliation,
and threats into a judge's own life.)

625
00:25:57,280 --> 00:25:58,669
(They are like shadows)

626
00:25:58,670 --> 00:26:00,640
(lurking behind the light.)

627
00:26:05,760 --> 00:26:06,629
Fei, what's wrong?

628
00:26:06,630 --> 00:26:07,709
Fei. Are you alright, Fei?

629
00:26:07,710 --> 00:26:09,079
Alright, alright. Calm down.

630
00:26:09,080 --> 00:26:10,640
Did you have a nightmare?

631
00:26:11,600 --> 00:26:12,840
Let me hold you.

632
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:15,669
Did you have a bad dream?
There, there. You're safe now.

633
00:26:15,670 --> 00:26:16,359
Fei.

634
00:26:16,360 --> 00:26:18,039
It's okay. Must've been a bad dream.

635
00:26:18,040 --> 00:26:19,400
It's okay.

636
00:26:22,800 --> 00:26:24,319
All good now.

637
00:26:24,320 --> 00:26:25,319
The child just fell asleep

638
00:26:25,320 --> 00:26:26,559
and had a dream, that's all.

639
00:26:26,560 --> 00:26:28,600
Please, carry on eating.

640
00:26:28,630 --> 00:26:30,389
- It's nothing.
- Carry on eating.

641
00:26:30,390 --> 00:26:32,470
Sorry about that.

642
00:26:40,280 --> 00:26:41,629
No trouble at all.

643
00:26:41,630 --> 00:26:43,279
You came all this way.

644
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:44,640
Please come in.

645
00:26:45,670 --> 00:26:47,400
Have a seat. Sit anywhere you want.

646
00:26:47,760 --> 00:26:49,840
I'll pour you some warm water.

647
00:26:53,390 --> 00:26:55,120
You don't have to.

648
00:26:56,190 --> 00:26:57,149
Mrs. Liu,

649
00:26:57,150 --> 00:26:58,559
you came all the way here.

650
00:26:58,560 --> 00:27:00,599
Nothing happened
to Xiaolongbao again, right?

651
00:27:00,600 --> 00:27:02,189
No, nothing at all.

652
00:27:02,190 --> 00:27:03,470
She's doing fine.

653
00:27:03,670 --> 00:27:04,950
Good to hear that.

654
00:27:05,670 --> 00:27:09,400
I made some xiaolongbao for you.

655
00:27:10,230 --> 00:27:11,629
Thank you, Mrs. Liu.

656
00:27:11,630 --> 00:27:13,759
I hope you don't dislike them.

657
00:27:13,760 --> 00:27:15,149
I went to the big supermarket

658
00:27:15,150 --> 00:27:16,389
to buy fresh meat.

659
00:27:16,390 --> 00:27:17,389
I didn't just make do.

660
00:27:17,390 --> 00:27:18,559
I understand.

661
00:27:18,560 --> 00:27:20,120
I like them, Mrs. Liu.

662
00:27:20,950 --> 00:27:22,799
It's all thanks to you and Judge Shen

663
00:27:22,800 --> 00:27:24,429
for taking care of my granddaughter.

664
00:27:24,430 --> 00:27:26,039
And thanks to you,

665
00:27:26,040 --> 00:27:26,759
we were able to

666
00:27:26,760 --> 00:27:29,189
get her back

667
00:27:29,190 --> 00:27:30,600
from that unreliable daughter-in-law.

668
00:27:30,840 --> 00:27:33,079
If my sweetheart had stayed with them,

669
00:27:33,080 --> 00:27:34,510
who knows

670
00:27:34,760 --> 00:27:37,709
how much she'd have suffered.

671
00:27:37,710 --> 00:27:39,359
It's what I should do.

672
00:27:39,360 --> 00:27:40,879
It's all for the child.

673
00:27:40,880 --> 00:27:43,389
You didn't really have a choice
when that happened.

674
00:27:43,390 --> 00:27:44,949
No one could just ignore it.

675
00:27:44,950 --> 00:27:46,270
I know

676
00:27:46,280 --> 00:27:48,680
my son hasn't paid you.

677
00:27:49,710 --> 00:27:50,519
My life's been so hard.

678
00:27:50,520 --> 00:27:53,469
How did I end up
with such an unfilial son?

679
00:27:53,470 --> 00:27:55,599
I don't even know what to say. I...

680
00:27:55,600 --> 00:27:57,310
I feel terrible. I...

681
00:27:57,430 --> 00:27:59,510
I don't know how to repay you.

682
00:27:59,600 --> 00:28:01,189
So I make xiaolongbao.

683
00:28:01,190 --> 00:28:02,909
Just a small skill of mine,

684
00:28:02,910 --> 00:28:05,149
but everyone who's tried them
says they're good.

685
00:28:05,150 --> 00:28:06,440
Give them a try.

686
00:28:09,280 --> 00:28:11,360
Oh, they're still warm.

687
00:28:11,800 --> 00:28:14,229
Mrs. Liu, you brought way too many.
You're too kind.

688
00:28:14,230 --> 00:28:16,360
There's enough here for me
to open a shop.

689
00:28:18,190 --> 00:28:21,640
This portion here is for Judge Shen.

690
00:28:21,910 --> 00:28:23,629
I prepared two boxes.

691
00:28:23,630 --> 00:28:25,119
I called him,

692
00:28:25,120 --> 00:28:27,119
but he wouldn't accept it,
no matter what.

693
00:28:27,120 --> 00:28:27,989
He told me

694
00:28:27,990 --> 00:28:30,039
not to wait outside the court either.

695
00:28:30,040 --> 00:28:32,710
There are rules that
they're not allowed to accept gifts.

696
00:28:33,280 --> 00:28:34,389
Yes, Mrs. Liu.

697
00:28:34,390 --> 00:28:36,669
Judges do have strict rules.

698
00:28:36,670 --> 00:28:38,039
It can be quite a hassle.

699
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:39,469
I haven't had lunch yet,

700
00:28:39,470 --> 00:28:40,389
and with so many here,

701
00:28:40,390 --> 00:28:41,709
I'm lucky to have them.

702
00:28:41,710 --> 00:28:43,039
I'll finish them in a bit.

703
00:28:43,040 --> 00:28:44,200
Alright then.

704
00:28:44,230 --> 00:28:46,389
Ms. Qin, I should get going.

705
00:28:46,390 --> 00:28:47,319
I asked a friend

706
00:28:47,320 --> 00:28:48,799
to keep an eye on Xiaolongbao.

707
00:28:48,800 --> 00:28:49,949
I need to head back.

708
00:28:49,950 --> 00:28:51,429
You haven't had your water yet.

709
00:28:51,430 --> 00:28:52,759
No need.

710
00:28:52,760 --> 00:28:54,599
Thank you again, young lady.

711
00:28:54,600 --> 00:28:55,839
I'll walk you out.

712
00:28:55,840 --> 00:28:58,359
No, it's fine. Focus on your work.
No need to walk me out.

713
00:28:58,360 --> 00:28:59,189
Thank you.

714
00:28:59,190 --> 00:29:01,279
Thank you for your hard work.
I'll get going.

715
00:29:01,280 --> 00:29:03,030
Take care, Mrs. Liu.

716
00:29:12,040 --> 00:29:13,640
(Xiaolongbao's Grandma)

717
00:29:14,560 --> 00:29:15,189
Hello, Mrs. Liu?

718
00:29:15,190 --> 00:29:17,119
I just opened the xiaolongbao
and was about to eat them.

719
00:29:17,120 --> 00:29:19,429
Sorry to bother you.

720
00:29:19,430 --> 00:29:21,149
I forgot to mention earlier.

721
00:29:21,150 --> 00:29:23,909
There are two small boxes on top.

722
00:29:23,910 --> 00:29:25,989
My granddaughter made those.

723
00:29:25,990 --> 00:29:27,359
She asked me to tell you

724
00:29:27,360 --> 00:29:30,710
she can already make
xiaolongbao at her age.

725
00:29:32,320 --> 00:29:34,079
They don't look very good,

726
00:29:34,080 --> 00:29:35,469
just take a look.

727
00:29:35,470 --> 00:29:37,270
The ones below are the proper ones.

728
00:29:38,600 --> 00:29:39,559
Thank you, Mrs. Liu.

729
00:29:39,560 --> 00:29:41,079
Please tell her

730
00:29:41,080 --> 00:29:42,229
they smell amazing

731
00:29:42,230 --> 00:29:43,600
and taste great.

732
00:29:44,230 --> 00:29:45,640
I will.

733
00:29:46,430 --> 00:29:48,359
Go ahead and get back to work.
I won't keep you any longer.

734
00:29:48,360 --> 00:29:49,790
Alright.

735
00:30:14,040 --> 00:30:16,559
The three of you are disputing

736
00:30:16,560 --> 00:30:17,599
over Mr. Yao's guardianship.

737
00:30:17,600 --> 00:30:19,279
Today, each of you can explain

738
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:21,149
why you are the most suitable guardian.

739
00:30:21,150 --> 00:30:22,189
Alright. Who wants to go first?

740
00:30:22,190 --> 00:30:23,279
- I'll go first.
- I'll go first.

741
00:30:23,280 --> 00:30:24,360
My brother...

742
00:30:24,390 --> 00:30:26,120
I'm his daughter.

743
00:30:26,190 --> 00:30:28,640
We're direct family.

744
00:30:28,910 --> 00:30:30,519
We are father and daughter.

745
00:30:30,520 --> 00:30:32,550
So when it comes to inheritance,

746
00:30:32,950 --> 00:30:35,669
it's only right that I come first.

747
00:30:35,670 --> 00:30:37,079
And it's natural for me

748
00:30:37,080 --> 00:30:38,790
to take care of him.

749
00:30:38,910 --> 00:30:40,799
That's my responsibility too.

750
00:30:40,800 --> 00:30:42,360
I'm his daughter.

751
00:30:43,190 --> 00:30:44,629
By blood,

752
00:30:44,630 --> 00:30:46,709
the daughter is no doubt the closest.

753
00:30:46,710 --> 00:30:48,989
But when it comes to inheritance,

754
00:30:48,990 --> 00:30:51,950
a spouse gets half, right?

755
00:30:51,990 --> 00:30:53,120
Also,

756
00:30:53,150 --> 00:30:54,680
the one taking care of him

757
00:30:54,800 --> 00:30:57,600
should be his spouse.

758
00:30:57,880 --> 00:30:58,799
Right?

759
00:30:58,800 --> 00:30:59,839
Should be you?

760
00:30:59,840 --> 00:31:01,079
Are you his wife?

761
00:31:01,080 --> 00:31:02,079
Are you legally married?

762
00:31:02,080 --> 00:31:03,429
You're just a caretaker.

763
00:31:03,430 --> 00:31:04,839
Who are you calling a caretaker?

764
00:31:04,840 --> 00:31:07,119
We've been together
for almost a year.

765
00:31:07,120 --> 00:31:08,879
If your dad hadn't fallen ill so suddenly,

766
00:31:08,880 --> 00:31:10,629
we'd have had our wedding.

767
00:31:10,630 --> 00:31:11,640
We even

768
00:31:11,950 --> 00:31:13,920
held a banquet in my hometown.

769
00:31:17,390 --> 00:31:18,469
Can you still have children?

770
00:31:18,470 --> 00:31:19,989
If you could,

771
00:31:19,990 --> 00:31:21,709
you'd probably be throwing

772
00:31:21,710 --> 00:31:23,360
a one-month birthday celebration
by now, right?

773
00:31:23,700 --> 00:31:24,959
- Are you even human?
- Of course I am.

774
00:31:24,959 --> 00:31:26,149
Can you speak like a decent person?

775
00:31:26,150 --> 00:31:27,629
I am speaking like a decent person.
Can you even understand?

776
00:31:27,630 --> 00:31:28,799
You call that decent?

777
00:31:28,800 --> 00:31:30,909
Why not? You think you'd
understand even if I did?

778
00:31:30,910 --> 00:31:32,750
No personal attacks.

779
00:31:38,320 --> 00:31:41,120
Your parents have been divorced
for forty years.

780
00:31:41,150 --> 00:31:42,669
You've been married three times

781
00:31:42,670 --> 00:31:45,310
and divorced three times.

782
00:31:45,560 --> 00:31:47,750
Why do you think your father
never acknowledged you?

783
00:31:47,950 --> 00:31:51,120
Because all you care about is money.

784
00:31:52,120 --> 00:31:52,799
Your Honor,

785
00:31:52,800 --> 00:31:53,839
she's insulting my love

786
00:31:53,840 --> 00:31:55,149
and my marriage.

787
00:31:55,150 --> 00:31:56,709
So what if I've been married three times?

788
00:31:56,710 --> 00:31:58,119
So what if I've divorced three times?

789
00:31:58,120 --> 00:31:59,789
- I have a marriage certificate. Do you?
- Both of you. Sit down.

790
00:31:59,790 --> 00:32:00,359
You!

791
00:32:00,360 --> 00:32:02,040
(Mediation Room, Camera 1)
Please calm yourselves.

792
00:32:02,040 --> 00:32:03,189
This is a court.

793
00:32:03,190 --> 00:32:04,600
Order, please.

794
00:32:04,760 --> 00:32:05,799
Sit down.

795
00:32:05,800 --> 00:32:07,230
One by one, please.

796
00:32:09,520 --> 00:32:10,640
Your Honor,

797
00:32:11,520 --> 00:32:12,880
I didn't grow up

798
00:32:15,560 --> 00:32:17,750
with my dad.

799
00:32:18,560 --> 00:32:19,790
So

800
00:32:19,950 --> 00:32:21,880
now that he's like this,

801
00:32:22,560 --> 00:32:24,030
I want to take care of him.

802
00:32:24,800 --> 00:32:26,550
I want to make up for it.

803
00:32:26,950 --> 00:32:28,149
What about you two?

804
00:32:28,150 --> 00:32:29,840
Who do you think you are?

805
00:32:29,880 --> 00:32:30,879
And you two,

806
00:32:30,880 --> 00:32:33,200
what are you to him?

807
00:32:33,670 --> 00:32:35,559
You're both halfway in the grave,

808
00:32:35,560 --> 00:32:36,669
and you're fighting me for this?

809
00:32:36,670 --> 00:32:37,709
Who's fighting you?

810
00:32:37,710 --> 00:32:39,669
I just want my share.

811
00:32:39,670 --> 00:32:41,669
I'm his spouse.

812
00:32:41,670 --> 00:32:42,989
Spouse?

813
00:32:42,990 --> 00:32:44,429
With that temper of yours,

814
00:32:44,430 --> 00:32:47,030
do you have the patience
to care for a bedridden elder?

815
00:32:49,670 --> 00:32:50,880
Your Honor,

816
00:32:51,710 --> 00:32:53,189
it's my fault.

817
00:32:53,190 --> 00:32:54,600
I'm sorry.

818
00:32:55,670 --> 00:32:58,360
I couldn't stand what she said.

819
00:32:58,670 --> 00:32:59,599
Judge Shen,

820
00:32:59,600 --> 00:33:01,079
I'm not usually like this.

821
00:33:01,080 --> 00:33:03,359
She pushed me to this point.

822
00:33:03,360 --> 00:33:03,909
Look at her...

823
00:33:03,910 --> 00:33:04,839
Enough. Stop acting.

824
00:33:04,840 --> 00:33:06,840
Stop acting already.

825
00:33:06,950 --> 00:33:07,599
Your Honor,

826
00:33:07,600 --> 00:33:09,909
let me take care of my brother.

827
00:33:09,910 --> 00:33:11,279
If you leave him with them,

828
00:33:11,280 --> 00:33:12,949
they'll drive him to death
in three days.

829
00:33:12,950 --> 00:33:15,550
Who do you think you are?

830
00:33:15,800 --> 00:33:17,200
Enough!

831
00:33:17,230 --> 00:33:20,669
It seems we won't reach
an agreement today

832
00:33:20,670 --> 00:33:22,149
on Mr. Yao's guardianship.

833
00:33:22,150 --> 00:33:24,389
I'll consult Mr. Yao himself

834
00:33:24,390 --> 00:33:25,750
and make a decision afterward.

835
00:33:25,800 --> 00:33:27,360
That's all for today.

836
00:33:28,630 --> 00:33:29,429
Right.

837
00:33:29,430 --> 00:33:31,840
The account was linked to your ID.

838
00:33:33,120 --> 00:33:35,559
Legally, it's considered
protected virtual property.

839
00:33:35,560 --> 00:33:36,950
But since it was before marriage,

840
00:33:37,560 --> 00:33:39,149
the woman can still request

841
00:33:39,150 --> 00:33:41,030
a share of any value
added after marriage.

842
00:33:41,990 --> 00:33:43,710
I'm not taking sides.

843
00:33:43,800 --> 00:33:45,640
I'm clarifying the situation.

844
00:33:47,120 --> 00:33:48,840
Why did they call drop?

845
00:33:49,360 --> 00:33:50,790
Jeez, forget it.

846
00:33:55,710 --> 00:33:56,799
Judge Shen!

847
00:33:56,800 --> 00:33:57,950
Judge Shen!

848
00:33:58,990 --> 00:34:00,400
This is for you.

849
00:34:02,800 --> 00:34:04,669
Ms. Qin, there are rules.

850
00:34:04,670 --> 00:34:06,429
Don't worry. This is not a bribe.

851
00:34:06,430 --> 00:34:08,310
This is from Xiaolongbao's grandma.

852
00:34:10,550 --> 00:34:12,040
Open it.

853
00:34:19,640 --> 00:34:22,389
There were eight in the box.

854
00:34:22,390 --> 00:34:24,719
I couldn't help myself and ate four.

855
00:34:24,720 --> 00:34:26,640
These four are saved for you.

856
00:34:27,240 --> 00:34:29,200
These are made
by the little girl Xiaolongbao.

857
00:34:30,320 --> 00:34:31,909
See? I told you.

858
00:34:31,910 --> 00:34:33,639
I could make dumplings at four.

859
00:34:33,640 --> 00:34:35,910
And this girl already knows
how to make xiaolongbao.

860
00:34:39,200 --> 00:34:40,830
Try one.

861
00:34:41,800 --> 00:34:44,029
Don't worry. I won't report you.

862
00:34:44,030 --> 00:34:45,520
No one's around anyway.

863
00:34:52,880 --> 00:34:54,109
How does it taste?

864
00:34:54,110 --> 00:34:55,350
Good?

865
00:34:58,110 --> 00:34:59,509
No regrets, right?

866
00:34:59,510 --> 00:35:02,790
I told you leaving Xiaolongbao
with Mrs. Liu was the right call.

867
00:35:04,160 --> 00:35:05,600
Oh, right, Judge Shen.

868
00:35:06,110 --> 00:35:08,239
I received the money

869
00:35:08,240 --> 00:35:09,680
from Ms. Liu Lihua.

870
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:11,239
Thank you for going easy on her

871
00:35:11,240 --> 00:35:12,830
and preserving her family.

872
00:35:16,070 --> 00:35:19,679
I don't see it as helping her.

873
00:35:19,680 --> 00:35:21,109
Why not?

874
00:35:21,110 --> 00:35:22,319
She doesn't want a divorce,

875
00:35:22,320 --> 00:35:24,279
but she also doesn't want anyone
to know that.

876
00:35:24,280 --> 00:35:25,949
You not only dismissed her case,

877
00:35:25,950 --> 00:35:27,429
but you also kept her secret.

878
00:35:27,430 --> 00:35:29,120
I respect her choice,

879
00:35:29,590 --> 00:35:31,549
but I don't agree with it.

880
00:35:31,550 --> 00:35:34,830
Keeping a broken marriage alive
after the husband cheated

881
00:35:35,070 --> 00:35:36,759
isn't necessarily a good thing.

882
00:35:36,760 --> 00:35:39,230
But you still have to respect
her opinion.

883
00:35:39,360 --> 00:35:40,719
If she doesn't want a divorce,

884
00:35:40,720 --> 00:35:42,120
what can we do?

885
00:35:42,590 --> 00:35:46,200
Not everyone has the courage
to face reality.

886
00:35:46,360 --> 00:35:48,389
Even stepping out of a bubble,

887
00:35:48,390 --> 00:35:49,989
it has to be done slowly.

888
00:35:49,990 --> 00:35:51,159
But everything in life

889
00:35:51,160 --> 00:35:53,160
comes with a price.

890
00:35:53,510 --> 00:35:55,480
If you want a better view,

891
00:35:55,680 --> 00:35:57,390
you have to get a little wet
in the rain.

892
00:35:58,950 --> 00:35:59,879
You're right.

893
00:35:59,880 --> 00:36:01,029
But do you remember

894
00:36:01,030 --> 00:36:02,589
the sashimi you treated me to
the other day?

895
00:36:02,590 --> 00:36:06,160
That was the most expensive,
best thing I've ever eaten.

896
00:36:06,390 --> 00:36:08,080
Guess what happened after.

897
00:36:08,320 --> 00:36:09,680
What happened?

898
00:36:11,510 --> 00:36:13,199
Don't tell me you got diarrhea?

899
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:14,430
Exactly.

900
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:16,029
Three whole days.

901
00:36:16,030 --> 00:36:18,069
That seafood restaurant's
quality is fine.

902
00:36:18,070 --> 00:36:19,469
I've eaten there many times.

903
00:36:19,470 --> 00:36:19,799
Right.

904
00:36:19,800 --> 00:36:21,759
But people are different.

905
00:36:21,760 --> 00:36:24,029
I grew up eating something that fine.

906
00:36:24,030 --> 00:36:26,509
I only ate things
like brown rice noodles,

907
00:36:26,510 --> 00:36:27,759
cabbage, and tofu.

908
00:36:27,760 --> 00:36:29,040
I never had anything like that.

909
00:36:29,430 --> 00:36:30,839
They're fine things,

910
00:36:30,840 --> 00:36:32,710
but my stomach can't handle them.

911
00:36:34,390 --> 00:36:36,509
Sounds like you overdid it.

912
00:36:36,510 --> 00:36:38,679
I did not.

913
00:36:38,680 --> 00:36:39,429
I could eat

914
00:36:39,430 --> 00:36:40,879
three boxes of xiaolongbao easily.

915
00:36:40,880 --> 00:36:42,389
If I hadn't saved these for you,

916
00:36:42,390 --> 00:36:43,830
they'd already be gone.

917
00:36:44,720 --> 00:36:46,750
They are mine.

918
00:36:48,280 --> 00:36:49,790
Quick hands, huh?

919
00:36:55,880 --> 00:36:59,759
Are you the owner of the vehicle Tian AD3596S
who called to make an appointment?

920
00:36:59,760 --> 00:37:00,960
Yes.

921
00:37:02,070 --> 00:37:04,560
Your total comes to 3,386 yuan.

922
00:37:04,720 --> 00:37:06,520
That includes both pickup and payment.

923
00:37:06,680 --> 00:37:07,909
Alright, thank you.

924
00:37:07,910 --> 00:37:09,200
You're welcome.

925
00:37:24,950 --> 00:37:26,159
May I ask

926
00:37:26,160 --> 00:37:29,600
how much force it takes
to break a side mirror?

927
00:37:29,910 --> 00:37:34,270
Usually, it gets damaged
during a strong impact while driving.

928
00:37:35,680 --> 00:37:39,029
What if a person bumped into it
or pushed it down?

929
00:37:39,030 --> 00:37:40,319
Uh.

930
00:37:40,320 --> 00:37:42,109
To be honest,
I don't see that very often.

931
00:37:42,110 --> 00:37:43,279
If it's done by hand,

932
00:37:43,280 --> 00:37:44,949
as long as it's not forced
or deliberately snapped,

933
00:37:44,950 --> 00:37:46,350
it usually wouldn't break.

934
00:37:48,950 --> 00:37:50,549
Your car has Sentry Mode, right?

935
00:37:50,550 --> 00:37:52,910
It records everything, 360 degrees.

936
00:37:53,800 --> 00:37:55,759
Right. I forgot about that. Thanks.

937
00:37:55,760 --> 00:37:57,080
Take care.

938
00:38:00,200 --> 00:38:02,920
(Sentry Mode)

939
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:20,710
(Qin Rui?)

940
00:38:29,840 --> 00:38:31,790
I now officially announce

941
00:38:31,880 --> 00:38:34,879
that the "Law into the Community" event
has begun.

942
00:38:34,880 --> 00:38:36,239
Bravo!

943
00:38:36,240 --> 00:38:37,639
As long as you provide a valid case,

944
00:38:37,640 --> 00:38:39,239
you'll get free eggs.

945
00:38:39,240 --> 00:38:40,429
First-come, first-served. Okay?

946
00:38:40,430 --> 00:38:41,029
Okay!

947
00:38:41,030 --> 00:38:42,279
Who's got a case?

948
00:38:42,280 --> 00:38:43,359
- Me!
- Me!

949
00:38:43,360 --> 00:38:44,469
Good. Who's first?

950
00:38:44,470 --> 00:38:44,949
Go ahead.

951
00:38:44,950 --> 00:38:47,949
My son starts work at 8 AM every day,
cooking hotpot base,

952
00:38:47,950 --> 00:38:49,719
and doesn't get home until midnight.

953
00:38:49,720 --> 00:38:51,239
He even works through Spring Festival

954
00:38:51,240 --> 00:38:52,909
and hasn't been paid a single dime
in overtime.

955
00:38:52,910 --> 00:38:55,270
Is that fair?

956
00:38:56,590 --> 00:38:58,719
That's a serious violation
of labor laws.

957
00:38:58,720 --> 00:39:01,239
Holiday overtime must be paid triple.

958
00:39:01,240 --> 00:39:02,879
Here's what we will do. Listen.

959
00:39:02,880 --> 00:39:03,469
Take this.

960
00:39:03,470 --> 00:39:05,759
My address and number are on it.

961
00:39:05,760 --> 00:39:06,799
Have your son contact me.

962
00:39:06,800 --> 00:39:08,549
I'll take care of it.

963
00:39:08,550 --> 00:39:09,109
Alright.

964
00:39:09,110 --> 00:39:10,389
If he gets divorced,

965
00:39:10,390 --> 00:39:11,509
I'll send him your way.

966
00:39:11,510 --> 00:39:12,639
The hotpot restaurant

967
00:39:12,640 --> 00:39:14,710
belongs to his father-in-law.

968
00:39:16,240 --> 00:39:17,509
He's working for his own family.

969
00:39:17,510 --> 00:39:18,759
Then that's a different story.

970
00:39:18,760 --> 00:39:19,989
Anyone else?

971
00:39:19,990 --> 00:39:21,200
I've got one case.

972
00:39:21,320 --> 00:39:22,560
Make some room.

973
00:39:23,200 --> 00:39:24,359
Let me tell you.

974
00:39:24,360 --> 00:39:26,120
My useless son-in-law

975
00:39:26,320 --> 00:39:27,679
does nothing all day.

976
00:39:27,680 --> 00:39:29,429
He came home late the other night,

977
00:39:29,430 --> 00:39:30,759
making a racket.

978
00:39:30,760 --> 00:39:32,390
My daughter got furious

979
00:39:32,550 --> 00:39:33,549
and said a few words.

980
00:39:33,550 --> 00:39:37,560
He kicked her right in the chest.

981
00:39:38,640 --> 00:39:41,390
He knocked one of her teeth out.

982
00:39:42,550 --> 00:39:44,120
That serious?

983
00:39:44,430 --> 00:39:46,109
Next time he does that,

984
00:39:46,110 --> 00:39:48,839
can I call the police
and have him arrested?

985
00:39:48,840 --> 00:39:50,719
That's domestic violence.

986
00:39:50,720 --> 00:39:51,639
Absolutely.

987
00:39:51,640 --> 00:39:52,429
Think about this.

988
00:39:52,430 --> 00:39:55,639
Losing a tooth counts as a minor injury.

989
00:39:55,640 --> 00:39:56,839
If the police don't act,

990
00:39:56,840 --> 00:39:58,469
you can file a lawsuit yourself.

991
00:39:58,470 --> 00:39:59,790
I see.

992
00:39:59,840 --> 00:40:01,960
How much compensation could she get?

993
00:40:02,280 --> 00:40:03,509
What's the maximum?

994
00:40:03,510 --> 00:40:04,029
Compensation?

995
00:40:04,030 --> 00:40:05,549
That's her dog.

996
00:40:05,550 --> 00:40:06,960
Always in heat.

997
00:40:07,160 --> 00:40:09,750
She barks at everyone
and chases kids around.

998
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:11,199
Not just her son-in-law,

999
00:40:11,200 --> 00:40:12,960
even I want to kick the dog.

1000
00:40:14,360 --> 00:40:15,870
A dog?

1001
00:40:16,880 --> 00:40:18,160
Ma'am,

1002
00:40:18,590 --> 00:40:21,509
the daughter mentioned is a dog?

1003
00:40:21,510 --> 00:40:22,469
What's wrong with that?

1004
00:40:22,470 --> 00:40:25,230
People have rights, dogs don't?

1005
00:40:26,760 --> 00:40:28,109
(People's Hospital,
Outpatient Department)

1006
00:40:28,110 --> 00:40:29,270
Mr. Yao.

1007
00:40:29,800 --> 00:40:30,830
Mr. Yao.

1008
00:40:31,550 --> 00:40:33,080
People from the court are here.

1009
00:40:37,110 --> 00:40:37,909
He's awake.

1010
00:40:37,910 --> 00:40:38,909
Thank you.

1011
00:40:38,910 --> 00:40:40,080
No problem.

1012
00:40:48,720 --> 00:40:50,989
Mr. Yao, hello.

1013
00:40:50,990 --> 00:40:52,509
We're from the Family Division

1014
00:40:52,510 --> 00:40:53,799
of Qingcheng District People's  Court.

1015
00:40:53,800 --> 00:40:55,159
My name is Shen Xiezhi.

1016
00:40:55,160 --> 00:40:58,200
I'm the presiding judge
on your guardianship case.

1017
00:40:58,360 --> 00:41:00,319
This is Chen Xianghui, the court clerk.

1018
00:41:00,320 --> 00:41:01,109
Hello.

1019
00:41:01,110 --> 00:41:04,389
I understand your condition
isn't very stable right now.

1020
00:41:04,390 --> 00:41:05,199
How about this?

1021
00:41:05,200 --> 00:41:08,520
If you can hear me, please blink.

1022
00:41:10,030 --> 00:41:10,989
Good.

1023
00:41:10,990 --> 00:41:12,429
We're here today

1024
00:41:12,430 --> 00:41:15,310
to understand your true wishes.

1025
00:41:15,510 --> 00:41:18,350
Given your current condition,

1026
00:41:18,360 --> 00:41:19,469
you may not be able

1027
00:41:19,470 --> 00:41:22,000
to take care of yourself.

1028
00:41:22,550 --> 00:41:24,429
You'll need a guardian.

1029
00:41:24,430 --> 00:41:25,960
Your three relatives.

1030
00:41:26,200 --> 00:41:28,109
To be precise, two relatives

1031
00:41:28,110 --> 00:41:31,480
and Ms. Wu, who's close to you,

1032
00:41:31,550 --> 00:41:34,230
all wish to take on that role.

1033
00:41:39,840 --> 00:41:41,200
What did you say?

1034
00:41:41,360 --> 00:41:42,549
I didn't catch that.

1035
00:41:42,550 --> 00:41:44,080
Could you repeat it?

1036
00:41:45,280 --> 00:41:46,279
I

1037
00:41:46,280 --> 00:41:47,750
want to die.

1038
00:42:02,800 --> 00:42:03,239
Ma'am,

1039
00:42:03,240 --> 00:42:05,719
there are generally two cases
under the law

1040
00:42:05,720 --> 00:42:07,759
where child support may not be paid.

1041
00:42:07,760 --> 00:42:10,319
One, if the paying party

1042
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:11,719
is chronically ill,

1043
00:42:11,720 --> 00:42:13,589
unable to work,

1044
00:42:13,590 --> 00:42:14,639
and has no income.

1045
00:42:14,640 --> 00:42:15,509
The other is

1046
00:42:15,510 --> 00:42:18,279
they have committed a crime

1047
00:42:18,280 --> 00:42:19,679
and are serving time.

1048
00:42:19,680 --> 00:42:21,469
But he has a BMW

1049
00:42:21,470 --> 00:42:24,319
and eats out every day,
gambles, and fools around.

1050
00:42:24,320 --> 00:42:26,200
Then you should definitely
go after him for support.

1051
00:42:27,070 --> 00:42:27,719
Well.

1052
00:42:27,720 --> 00:42:29,679
Give me your daughter's number.

1053
00:42:29,680 --> 00:42:31,159
181118

1054
00:42:31,160 --> 00:42:32,790
9018.

1055
00:42:33,110 --> 00:42:34,239
She's at work.

1056
00:42:34,240 --> 00:42:35,199
You can call her later.

1057
00:42:35,200 --> 00:42:36,710
I'll call when I get back.

1058
00:42:36,950 --> 00:42:39,799
Leave your granddaughter's support to me.

1059
00:42:39,800 --> 00:42:40,199
Alright.

1060
00:42:40,200 --> 00:42:42,560
- Can you start giving out the eggs now?
- Right.

1061
00:42:42,640 --> 00:42:43,589
Sure, no problem.

1062
00:42:43,590 --> 00:42:44,949
No rush.

1063
00:42:44,950 --> 00:42:46,199
Take this.

1064
00:42:46,200 --> 00:42:47,639
Cook some noodles

1065
00:42:47,640 --> 00:42:49,909
and crack an egg in.

1066
00:42:49,910 --> 00:42:52,469
After all that talking,

1067
00:42:52,470 --> 00:42:54,000
I only get one egg?

1068
00:42:56,280 --> 00:42:57,589
There are four people in my family.

1069
00:42:57,590 --> 00:42:59,359
We would need one each.

1070
00:42:59,360 --> 00:43:00,870
That's right.

1071
00:43:00,910 --> 00:43:01,839
Don't grab the eggs.

1072
00:43:01,840 --> 00:43:03,310
No grabbing!

1073
00:43:03,700 --> 00:43:04,620
Look at that.

1074
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

1075
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

1076
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

1077
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1078
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1079
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1080
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

1081
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

1082
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

1083
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

1084
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

1085
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1086
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1087
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1088
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

1089
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

1090
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

1091
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

1092
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

1093
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,810
♪To answer those voices♪

1094
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,240
♪You deserve to be happy♪

1095
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,990
♪Loud and clear♪

1096
00:44:34,990 --> 00:44:37,310
♪All the little things♪

1097
00:44:37,310 --> 00:44:40,010
♪Woven into our lives♪

1098
00:44:40,830 --> 00:44:42,880
♪The building blocks of life♪

1099
00:44:42,880 --> 00:44:44,590
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1100
00:44:44,590 --> 00:44:47,040
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1101
00:44:47,040 --> 00:44:49,150
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1102
00:44:49,400 --> 00:44:51,530
♪Some questions♪

1103
00:44:52,100 --> 00:44:54,800
♪Weigh like mountains♪

1104
00:44:57,690 --> 00:45:02,840
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1105
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:07,130
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1106
00:45:07,310 --> 00:45:12,360
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1107
00:45:12,730 --> 00:45:16,430
♪Where fairness stands♪

1108
00:45:16,600 --> 00:45:19,680
♪Within the law♪

1109
00:45:20,840 --> 00:45:29,520
♪And within every heart♪
